-delay <1/100ths of a second>
display the next image after pausing
This option is useful for regulating the animation of image sequencesDelay/100
seconds must expire before the display of the next image. The default is no
delay between each showing of the image sequence. The maximum delay is 65535.
You can specify a delay range (e.g. -delay 10-500) which sets the minimum and
maximum delay.
